  <p>I'm trying to make a Chrome extension which runs a script whenever the user opens a new tab.  </p>  <p>I have the following basic code which is supposed to just paint the page red whenever the extension button is clicked.  </p>  <p>It seems to work fine when I navigate to an actual website (ex: here on stackoverflow.com, click my extension icon, page becomes red).  However, if I just create a brand new tab and click the button, the popup loads but the page never changes color. </p>  <p>manifest.json:</p>  <pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>{   "manifest_version": 2,   "name": "ConsoleTap",   "version": "0.1.0",   "browser_action": {     "default_icon": "icon.png",     "default_popup": "menu.html"   },   "permissions": [     "tabs",     "&lt;all_urls&gt;",     "https://ajax.googleapis.com/"   ] }   </code></pre>  <p>menu.html:</p>  <pre class="lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;!doctype html&gt; &lt;html&gt;     &lt;head&gt;         &lt;script src="menu.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;     &lt;/head&gt;     &lt;body&gt;         hello     &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>menu.js:</p>  <pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {     chrome.tabs.executeScript(null,{code:"document.body.style.backgroundColor='red'"}); });   </code></pre>  <p>Any ideas on why the page won't update the background color on a new tab?  I'm guessing the <code>DOMContentLoaded</code> is never fired or it's listening after the load occurs somehow?</p>